{"title_page": "Oberharz (Samtgemeinde)", "text_new": "{{about||the town in Harz district|Oberharz am Brocken}}\n\n{{Infobox German location\n|name               = Oberharz\n|type                = Samtgemeinde\n|image_photo        = <!-- Representative photo of location -->\n|imagesize          = <!-- Photo size. Default is 250px -->\n|image_caption      = <!-- Photo caption -->\n|image_coa             = Wappen Samtgemeinde Oberharz.png\n|coordinates        = {{coord|51|48|11|N|10|19|58|E|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n|image_plan           = <!-- Image displaying location in more detail (eg. location within state or district -->\n|plantext = <!-- Description of image \"Lageplan\" Default: \"Location of XX\" -->\n|state         = Lower Saxony\n|district          = Goslar\n|elevation               = 560\n|area             = 43.63\n|population          = 15769 \n|Stand              = 2013-12-31<ref>{{cite web|title=Bev\u00f6lkerungsfortschreibung|url=http://www1.nls.niedersachsen.de/statistik/|author=Nieders\u00e4chsisches Landesamt f\u00fcr Statistik |language=German}}</ref>\n|postal_code                = 38678, 38707, 38709\n|area_code            = 05323, 05328, 05329\n|licence                = GS\n|Gemeindeschl\u00fcssel  = \n|divisions         = 4 [[municipalities]]\n|website            = [http://www.samtgemeinde-oberharz.de/ www.samtgemeinde-<br />oberharz.de]\n|year               = 1972\n|dissolved = January 2015\n|_noautocat = yes\n}}\n\n'''Oberharz''' is a former ''[[Samtgemeinde]]'' (\"collective municipality\") in the [[Goslar (district)|district of Goslar]], in [[Lower Saxony]], [[Germany]]. It was situated in the western part of the [[Harz]], approx. 15&nbsp;km southwest of [[Goslar]]. Its seat was in the town [[Clausthal-Zellerfeld]]. It was disbanded in January 2015, when its member municipalities merged into the town Clausthal-Zellerfeld.\n\nThe ''Samtgemeinde'' Oberharz consisted of the following municipalities:\n\n* [[Altenau, Lower Saxony|Altenau]]\n* [[Clausthal-Zellerfeld]] \n* [[Schulenberg im Oberharz]]\n* [[Wildemann]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n[[Category:Former Samtgemeinden in Lower Saxony]]\n[[Category:Goslar (district)]]\n\n\n{{Goslar-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{about||the town in Harz district|Oberharz am Brocken}}\n\n{{Infobox German location\n|name               = Oberharz\n|type                = Samtgemeinde\n|image_photo        = <!-- Representative photo of location -->\n|imagesize          = <!-- Photo size. Default is 250px -->\n|image_caption      = <!-- Photo caption -->\n|image_coa             = Wappen Samtgemeinde Oberharz.png\n|coordinates        = {{coord|51|48|11|N|10|19|58|E|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n|Karte              = <!-- Only when the automatic locator (needs co-ordinates) does not work -->\n|image_plan           = <!-- Image displaying location in more detail (eg. location within state or district -->\n|plantext = <!-- Description of image \"Lageplan\" Default: \"Location of XX\" -->\n|state         = Lower Saxony\n|district          = Goslar\n|elevation               = 560\n|area             = 43.63\n|population          = 15769 \n|Stand              = 2013-12-31\n|pop_ref            = <ref>{{cite web|title=Bev\u00f6lkerungsfortschreibung|url=http://www1.nls.niedersachsen.de/statistik/|author=Nieders\u00e4chsisches Landesamt f\u00fcr Statistik |language=German}}</ref>\n|postal_code                = 38678, 38707, 38709\n|PLZ-alt            = <!-- Older postcode(s) - only when available - WILL NOT BE DISPLAYED-->\n|area_code            = 05323, 05328, 05329\n|licence                = GS\n|Gemeindeschl\u00fcssel  = \n|NUTS               = <!-- NUTS value: DEXXX  - WILL NOT BE DISPLAYED -->\n|LOCODE             = <!-- UN/LOCODE value: \"DE XXX\"  - WILL NOT BE DISPLAYED -->\n|divisions         = 4 [[municipalities]]\n|Adresse-Verband    = An der Marktkirche 8<br />38678 Clausthal-Zellerfeld\n|website            = [http://www.samtgemeinde-oberharz.de/ www.samtgemeinde-<br />oberharz.de]\n|mayor      = Walter Lampe\n|B\u00fcrgermeistertitel = [[B\u00fcrgermeister|Samtgemeinde-<br />b\u00fcrgermeister]]\n|party             = SPD\n|ruling_party1      = <!-- Leading political party currently in power - give abbreviations -->\n|ruling_party2      = <!-- 2nd ruling political party - give abbreviations -->\n|ruling_party3      = <!-- 3rd ruling political party - give abbreviations -->\n|year               = 1972\n|dissolved = yes\n|_noautocat = yes\n}}\n\n'''Oberharz''' is a former ''[[Samtgemeinde]]'' (\"collective municipality\") in the [[Goslar (district)|district of Goslar]], in [[Lower Saxony]], [[Germany]]. It was situated in the western part of the [[Harz]], approx. 15&nbsp;km southwest of [[Goslar]]. Its seat was in the town [[Clausthal-Zellerfeld]]. It was disbanded in January 2015, when its member municipalities merged into the town Clausthal-Zellerfeld.\n\nThe ''Samtgemeinde'' Oberharz consisted of the following municipalities:\n\n* [[Altenau, Lower Saxony|Altenau]]\n* [[Clausthal-Zellerfeld]] \n* [[Schulenberg im Oberharz]]\n* [[Wildemann]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n[[Category:Former Samtgemeinden in Lower Saxony]]\n[[Category:Goslar (district)]]\n\n\n{{Goslar-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Markussep", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oberharz_(Samtgemeinde)"}
{"title_page": "Never Seen the Rain", "text_new": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = Never Seen the Rain\n| cover      = Never Seen the Rain by Tones and I.png\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Tones and I]]\n| EP         = [[The Kids Are Coming]]\n| released   = {{start date|2019|07|16|df=yes}}\n| format     = {{hlist|[[Music download|Digital download]]|[[Streaming media|streaming]]}}\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = \n| length     = {{Duration|m=3|s=20}}\n| label      = Bad Batch\n| writer     =\n| producer   = [[Konstantin Kersting]]\n| prev_title = [[Dance Monkey]]\n| prev_year  = 2019\n| next_title = [[The Kids Are Coming (song)|The Kids Are Coming]]\n| next_year  = 2019\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|UdRJY-jlEhQ|\"Never Seen the Rain\"}}}}\n}}\n\n\"'''Never Seen the Rain'''\" is a song by Australian singer [[Tones and I]], released in Australia on 16 July 2019 as the third single from Tones and I's debut EP ''[[The Kids Are Coming]]''. Upon release Tones and I said \"[It's] about people who live the same repetitive life in fear of failure. So, they never try.\"<ref name=\"FirstSpin\">{{cite web|url=https://www.abc.net.au/triplej/news/musicnews/tones-and-i-new-song-never-seen-rain-debut-ep-kids-are-coming/11312586|title=First Spin: Tones And I continues winning streak with 'Never Seen The Rain'|publisher=ABC|date=16 July 2019 |accessdate=18 May 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://musicfeeds.com.au/news/listen-to-a-new-song-from-tones-and-i-never-seen-the-rain/|title= Listen To A New Song From Tones And I, \u2018Never Seen The Rain\u2019|publisher=Music Feeds|date=16 July 2019|accessdate=20 July 2019}}</ref> \nIn January 2020, the single was released outside of Australia. In February, it achieved gold status in New Zealand.\n\n==Critical reception==\nAl Newstead from ABC said \"'Never Seen the Rain' retains her keen pop sensibilities but wraps those distinctive vocals into an uplifting chorus.\"<ref name=\"FirstSpin\"/>\n\n==Music video==\nThe music video was produced by Visible Studios, directed by Nick Kozakis and Liam Kelly, and released on 7 August 2019.\n\n==Personnel==\nCredits adapted from [[AllMusic]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/never-seen-the-rain-mw0003309292/credits|title=Never Seen The Rain - Tones and I|publisher=AllMusic|accessdate=16 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n* [[Tones and I|Toni Watson]] \u2013 composer\n* [[Konstantin Kersting]] \u2013 mixing, production\n* Andrei Eremin \u2013 mastering\n\n==Charts==\n===Weekly charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2019\u20132020)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{single chart|Australia|7|artist=Tones and I|song=Never Seen the Rain|rowheader=true|accessdate=8 January 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Austria|70|artist=Tones and I|song=Never Seen the Rain|rowheader=true|accessdate=2 April 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Flanders|7|artist=Tones and I|song=Never Seen the Rain|rowheader=true|accessdate=14 March 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Wallonia|4|artist=Tones and I|song=Never Seen the Rain|rowheader=true|accessdate=10 April 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| France ([[Syndicat National de l'\u00c9dition Phonographique|SNEP]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://snepmusique.com/les-tops/le-top-de-la-semaine/top-albums/?semaine=12?&annee=2020&categorie=Top%20Singles|title=Top Singles (Week 12, 2020)|publisher=[[Syndicat National de l'\u00c9dition Phonographique]]|language=French|accessdate=24 March 2020}}</ref>\n| 60\n|-\n{{single chart|Germany2|51|songid=1893470|artist=Tones and I|song=Never Seen the Rain|rowheader=true|accessdate=3 April 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Ireland ([[Irish Recorded Music Association|IRMA]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://irma.ie/index.cfm?page=irish-charts&chart=Singles|title=IRMA \u2013 Irish Charts|publisher=[[Irish Recorded Music Association]]|accessdate=14 March 2020}}</ref>\n| 21\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Lithuania